SARAH HYLAND x CRITICS CHOICE 2023 

To start Sarah’s nail look for tonight, I used @apresnailofficial’s Ionic Gel to sculpt her nails into an almond shape. 

Second, we decided on a neutral natural base. This formula was 3 parts ionic gel, one part We Wheat Again.

Third, with color Royal Stamp I created a V shape French + I used @apresnailofficial’s Artiste Gel Liner brush help with the crisp detailing.

Finally, I gave Sarah a matte finish instead of our usual high shine glossy finish ✨

ELIZABETH OLSEN x OSCARS 

The key to any Oscar Worthy red carpet nail look is proper prep! I used @kissproducts Before & After Kit to help me prep Elizabeth’s nails. It includes a mini file, a prep and after pad, a buffer, a care pad and a care tool. Everything you’d need to prep your nails!

@kissproducts Manicovery Recovery Care Kit is great as a base to use if you have a little damage under nail polish or by itself! The nail masks nourish the nails while the cream helps to strengthen and the cuticle oil hydrates your nails!

After polishing her nails with a custom curated nail color, I topped her off with manicovery Nail and Cuticle Repair pen which also helps hydrate the nails for a picture perfect manicure!

When BabyLieu3 came into this world, my world shook in unimaginable ways. My sister gave birth to a beautiful child. A child she had nurtured, wanted, loved and carried for the past 9 months and within hours of delivery, my sister left earth side. 

I had reassured her, just one week before that, Buddha forbid, something happens and she’s not around, that I would do EVERYTHING in my power to love and care for her children in ways she would. Never in a million years could we have imagined we’d lose her. So…I pulled my boot straps up and got to mothering the best way I knew how at 24. 

June 18th, 2012 I became a mom. My identity, the trajectory of my life and my heart changed. I fully immersed my life into that role and not much has changed since. Almost 11 years later, the kids are no longer kids. They’ve grown and move through life with such speed and passion. 

Becoming a mother is more than what we see on the surface. I am blessed to have all the angels in my life that fuel me on days that I’m running on empty. My sister hovers over me everyday, especially when the days are hard. I am eternally grateful for the village that rallied for me, that stood by me, that consistently poured love into me. It was because of the relentlessness from my village that I was able to draw the strength and will I needed. 

Today I think about the blessings motherhood has shown me. Today I am grateful for my sister that gave me this privilege. Today, I want to say to my village…I see you. I love you. And this journey would not be the same without you.

Join me. 

I am sure by now you’ve all heard about the devastation in Maui. The wildfires has left so many people without home, shelter, food, clothing and for some, life. Multiple wildfires affected Lahaina, Kihei and Upcountry Maui. Thousands of people have been evacuated, most without shelter and the death toll currently is just under 100 and that’s only 20% of the affected zone. Maui’s wildfires were 100% contained as of Saturday and rescuers have remain there around the clock for search and rescue. 

Help me help Maui. 

Xoxo,
Thuy

#mauistrong #maui #dolkii #thuybnguyen #aframeagency

Maui, we love you and we hear you ❤️❤️❤️.

What started as just me shipping @dolkii clothing direct to families who emailed us (see previous post) has evolved into a much bigger initiative in partnership with @thuybnguyen. Thanks to continuous generous donations from her network & our community here in South Bay, we’re able to include additional essentials like N95 masks, toiletries, baby items, chapstick, sunscreen, gift cards and more into each package shipped. We’re maximizing each and every shipment in hopes of giving families as many clothes in sizes they’ve requested + essential items as we can possibly fit into each box. 

Speaking of shipping, thank you SO much to everyone who has sponsored our shipping fees. (tagged below ❤️✨). Instead of shipping everything in bulk to a donation center, we’re shipping DIRECTLY to every family / individual that emails us in hopes that these items get into their hands faster. I’m still trying to figure out a way to have our shipping charges covered or waived (@shopify I’m putting you on the spot here!!!!) that way these monetary donations can be reallocated directly to maui familys’ venmo accounts. We’ll keep trying ✊🏽❤️. 

We’re working away to ship these care packages out every day as donations get dropped off. And we’d like to get these out to families in need as quickly as possible so I won’t be posting much updates here. So if you see this post and have been affected by (or know someone who is affected by) the Maui fires, please email us at aloha@dolkii.com. Provide your name, clothing sizes and an address to ship to. If you need any other essential items please don’t hesitate to ask and we will do our best to include them in your care package. ❤️❤️❤️.

xo, Shaiyanne & Thuy

✨ Happy Tuesday!! ✨

Here is a little story for you behind this smile:

At the beginning of this year, I promised myself (+husband) that I would invest into myself where I invested in others. Why didn’t I do that this entire time? Well, ask any parent and their answer will always be our kids ♥️

After struggling the past three years with doing everything (and I mean, we did quite a lot) I possibly could to conceive a child, my body propelled me in every direction possible, except for the one I actually wanted. Or so I thought.

THIS direction was something I did not know I needed. The course correction had so much POWER and RESILIENCE behind it. It showed me who I could be for me. Not for anyone else or for any of life’s roles that I contribute to every day. This was JUST FOR ME. I really showed up for myself this year and I encourage each of you to do the same. Choose you, choose love, choose health. Do it for you. Everyday. 

I never knew a love like this existed. I heard about it but now experiencing it, I just want to bottle it up and sprinkle it everywhere I go. I know, it’s hard. I truly feel it every day. But everyday I chose myself, my kids saw, heard and experienced. What better way to lead your pack than to practice what you preach.

In every facet of life and in every endeavor, I will always choose ME ♥️ 

*just like being picked for a team, you never want to be the last pick… and let that FULLY sink in*

With so much gratitude,
💋 Thuy
